-- Toyota May Produce Small Hybrid Cars in Iwate, Miyagi, Yomiuri Reports
-- Tak Kumakura
-- 2010-07-22T21:51:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/toyota-may-produce-small-hybrid-cars-in-iwate-miyagi-yomiuri-reports.html

          
          
             Toyota Motor Corp. is considering
producing small hybrid vehicles in Iwate, northern Japan, as
well as in the neighboring prefecture of Miyagi, the Yomiuri
newspaper reported, citing the company.  
 The companyâ€™s Miyagi plant, which has an annual production
capacity of 120,000 vehicles, will start operations in January.
The factory in Iwate has an annual capacity of 300,000 units,
the newspaper said.   
          
          


  


        